Whereas in less severe cases of HPE, babies are born with
			 normal or near-normal brain development and facial deformities that may affect
			 the eyes, nose, and upper lip;

Whereas HPE affects approximatley 1 out of every 250
			 pregnancies during early embryo development, with many of those pregnancies
			 ending in miscarriage;

Whereas there is no standard course of treatment for HPE
			 because treatment must be individualized to the unique degree of malformations
			 of each child;
